WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:01.180
CHAPTER XXVII.

00:10.210 --> 00:16.160
BOST NOT THYSELF OF TOMORROW, FOR THOU KNOWEST NOT WHAT A DAY MAY BRING FORTH.

00:16.960 --> 00:22.980
Let another man praise thee, and not thine own mouth, A stranger, and not thine own lips.

00:24.500 --> 00:31.470
A stone is heavy, and the sand weighty, But a fool's wrath is heavier than them both.

00:33.540 --> 00:40.320
Wrath is cruel, and anger is outrageous, But who is able to stand before envy?

00:42.280 --> 00:48.500
Open rebuke is better than secret love. Faithful are the wounds of a friend,

00:48.500 --> 00:56.420
But the kisses of an enemy are deceitful. The full soul loatheth in honeycomb,

00:57.700 --> 01:01.320
But to the hungry soul every bitter thing is sweet.

01:02.580 --> 01:07.900
As a bird that wandereth from her nest, So is a man that wandereth from his place.

01:09.980 --> 01:15.980
Ointment and perfume rejoice the heart, So doth the sweetness of a man's friend by

01:18.720 --> 01:23.240
Thy known friend, and thy father's friend forsake not,

01:24.240 --> 01:27.560
Neither go into thy brother's house in the day of thy calamity,

01:27.840 --> 01:31.660
For better is a neighbor that is near than a brother far off.

01:32.620 --> 01:40.500
My son, be wise, and make my heart glad, That I may answer him that reproacheth me.

01:41.840 --> 01:45.740
A prudent man foreseeeth the evil and hideeth himself,

01:46.420 --> 01:48.640
But the simple pass on and are punished.

01:50.740 --> 01:57.000
Take his garment that is surety for a stranger, And take a pledge of him for a strange woman.

01:58.500 --> 02:02.360
He that blesseth a friend with a loud voice rising early in the morning,

02:02.660 --> 02:09.280
It shall be counted a curse to him. A continual dropping in a very rainy day,

02:09.280 --> 02:14.820
And a contentious woman are alike. Whosoever hideeth her hideeth the wind,

02:15.520 --> 02:19.500
And the ointment of his right hand which bereth itself.

02:21.220 --> 02:26.740
Iron sharpeneth iron, so a man sharpeneth the countenance of his friend.

02:28.140 --> 02:31.440
Whoso keepeth the fig tree shall eat the fruit thereof,

02:32.060 --> 02:35.680
So he that waiteth on his master shall be honored.

02:38.100 --> 02:43.200
As in water face answereth to face, so the heart of man to man.

02:44.980 --> 02:50.380
Hell and destruction are never full, so the eyes of man are never satisfied.

02:52.360 --> 02:56.220
As the finding pot for silver, and the furnace for gold,

02:56.540 --> 02:58.520
So is a man to his praise.

02:59.540 --> 03:04.080
Though thou shouldest bray a fool in a mortar among wheat with a pestle,

03:04.080 --> 03:07.740
Yet will not his foolishness depart from him.

03:08.540 --> 03:11.420
Be thou diligent to know the state of thy flocks,

03:11.660 --> 03:15.420
And look well to thy herds, for riches are not forever.

03:16.180 --> 03:18.680
And doth the crown endure to every generation?

03:19.600 --> 03:23.260
The hay appearth, and the tender grass showeth itself,

03:23.800 --> 03:25.880
And the herbs of the mountains are gathered,

03:26.280 --> 03:31.040
The lambs are for thy clothing, and the goats are the price of the field.

03:31.820 --> 03:34.880
And thou shalt have goat's milk enough for thy food,

03:35.640 --> 03:40.260
For the food of thy household, and for the maintenance of thy maidens.

